52.4	1982_Lebanon_War	1982 Lebanon War	The 1982 Lebanon War by Israel, and later known in Israel as the Lebanon War and First Lebanon War, began on 6 June 1982, when the Israel Defense Forces invaded southern Lebanon. The Government of Israel launched the military operation after the Abu Nidal Organization's assassination attempt against Israel's ambassador to the United Kingdom, Shlomo Argov.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Troepen_idf.jpg/300px-Troepen_idf.jpg
